Yes, she was very beautiful.

107
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:09,440
But that was definitely a man.

108
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:12,260
I see.

109
00:07:13,940 --> 00:07:16,420
So tell me, what's your name?

110
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,240
I'm Milosh.

111
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:21,420
I wonder, have we met somewhere before?

112
00:07:21,860 --> 00:07:22,120
Huh?

113
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,060
Uh-uh.

114
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:27,320
What were you doing when I saw you?

115
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:28,900
Nothing.

116
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:34,020
I know your face. You walk around this neighborhood a lot, don't you?

117
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:38,120
What is it you're looking for?

118
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:42,300
I... look for... my mom.

119
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:47,800
Why don't you have a seat and make yourself comfortable? Here, have some juice.

120
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:53,920
So, are you about to move out?

121
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:55,820
Why do you ask?

122
00:07:56,220 --> 00:08:00,220
Because you have that big bag, and there's no stuff in this room.

123
00:08:06,380 --> 00:08:09,340
So your mother, she's somewhere around here?

124
00:08:09,740 --> 00:08:10,020
Huh?

125
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:14,060
Your mother. You told me you were looking for her, isn't that right?

126
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,780
Yeah, but I don't really know if she lives here.

127
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:22,080
Then how will you find her? Do you have her picture?

128
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,060
Uh-uh. How come?

129
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:27,560
Too bad. You don't even know her face.

130
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:31,020
I'll know her. I'll know my mom when I see her face.

131
00:08:31,180 --> 00:08:33,060
No one at the orphanage believes me either.

132
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:35,380
They all keep telling me it's not gonna happen.

133
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:38,600
But when I see her, I'm gonna know her face for sure.

134
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:39,660
Count on it!

135
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:40,880
Really?

136
00:08:41,780 --> 00:08:44,420
Yeah. And my mom will know it's me when she sees me.

137
00:08:51,460 --> 00:08:57,020
"Even if you did find your mother, what if she acts like she doesn't know you?"

138
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:58,160
"Huh?"

139
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:02,260
"Think you were born because you were wanted?"

140
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:06,900
"I mean, why were you abandoned?"

141
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:12,380
"Could it be that your mother left you because she hated you?"

142
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:14,900
"No way!"

143
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:18,900
There's nothing special about being born not a thing

144
00:09:20,140 --> 00:09:23,540
Most of the universe is just death nothing more

145
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:32,880
In this universe of ours the birth of a new life on some corner of our planet is nothing but a tiny insignificant flash

146
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:35,340
Death is a normal thing

147
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,660
So why live?

148
00:09:39,140 --> 00:09:40,660
You think you were wanted

149
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,320
(eerie music)

150
00:09:44,260 --> 00:09:45,380
